    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "Canastota’s name derives from the Oneida term “Kniste Stota,” meaning “cluster of pines near still waters.”",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        11
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Canastota%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Construction of the Erie Canal began through Canastota in 1817, and by 1825 the village became a busy trade stop between Rome and Syracuse.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        27,
        18
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
